result.execSummary:
The defendant Ryan D Jarosinski was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Ryan D Jarosinski is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Ryan D Jarosinski was found guilty of Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Telephone conference on July 13, 2016 at 08:45 am.
Marquette County DNA Proof of Submission

Defendant Ryan D Jarosinski in court with attorney Roger L. Klopp.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
15CF83, 15CM122, 15CT45 & 15TR2149 tracking:
  Atty Hendee states plea agreement to Ct. 1 in 15CF83 & Ct. 1 in 15CM122.  Counts 2, 3 & 4 in 15CF83, Count 2 in 15CM122, 15CT45 and 15TR2149 to be dismissed.  Atty Hendee states that there is an argued jail sentence and the State is not objecting to expunge with conditions on the felony case only.  Atty Hendee states that the parties are not requesting a PSI be ordered.  Atty Klopp agrees.  Defendant agrees and enters a No Contest plea.
  Court questions defendant regarding plea. Advises of Constitutional Rights and elements of the charge.  Court finds plea made knowingly, voluntarily & Intelligently.

  BY THE COURT:  Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charges.  Court accepts defendant's plea and finds defendant guilty of Ct. 1 in 15CF83 & Ct. 1 in 15CM122.  Counts 2, 3 & 4 in 15CF83, Count 2 in 15CM122, 15CT45 and 15TR2149 to be dismissed.

Atty Hendee makes sentencing recommendations.
Atty Klopp makes sentencing arguments.

BY THE COURT:  15CF83:  Ct. 1:  Withhold Sentence; 24 months Probation with conditions:
60 days in the Marquette County Jail w/huber
  Report on or before May 9, 2016 by 7:00pm, clean & sober.
Court Costs = $268.00
DNA Sample + $250.00 Surcharge
Comply with any and all counseling recommended by the Agent
Counts 2, 3 & 4 to be dismissed.
No PSI ordered.
Credit will be determined by stipulation between counsel.
  If after 24 months the defendant has paid the fine and costs in full and has had no criminal violations, the defendant may petition the court for Expungement 973.015.
  **Court advises defendant that they have been convicted of a Felony and advises rights of voting privileges and of owning a firearm.

15CM122:  Ct. 1:  Withhold Sentence; 24 months Probation with conditions:
Court Costs = $243.00
DNA Sample + $200.00 Surcharge
Comply with any and all counseling recommended by the Agent
Ct. 2 to be dismissed.

15CT45 to be dismissed.
15TR2149 to be dismissed.

*Bonds on file to be applied and any balance to be returned.

Defendant Ryan D Jarosinski in court with attorney Roger L. Klopp.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
15CM122, 15CT45, 15CF83 and 15TR2149 tracking together:
Atty Hendee states that in the last hearing the State needed time to file the information; now that has been done.   Atty Klopp states that the Defendant received a copy of the information & waives it's reading.    Defendant stands mute.  Attorney request the Court enter a Not Guilty plea on behalf of the defendant.

  BY THE COURT:  Court enters a Not Guilty plea on behalf of the defendant.
Set for Return.
bond continued.  Return date scheduled for May 4, 2016 at 03:30 pm.

Defendant Ryan D Jarosinski in court with attorney Roger L. Klopp.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
15CM122 & 15CT45 tracking together:
Atty Hendee states that an offer was provided; however, Atty Klopp would like a revision to the offer and asks for more time.
Atty Klopp asks that the return date be reset.

BY THE COURT:  Reset
bond continued.  Return date scheduled for January 20, 2016 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Ryan D Jarosinski in court with attorney Mark Jay Gumz.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
15CM122 & 15CT45 tracking:

BY THE COURT:  Reset.
bond continued.  Return date scheduled for December 3, 2015 at 01:45 pm.

Defendant Ryan D Jarosinski in court with attorney Mark Jay Gumz.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty Gumz states that the Defendant received a copy of the criminal complaint & waives it's reading. Court finds probable cause.   Atty Gumz enters a Not Guilty plea.

  BY THE COURT:   Not Guilty plea entered.
bond continued.

Atty Gumz asks that 15CT45 track with this.
BY THE COURT:  So ordered.  Return date scheduled for November 4, 2015 at 02:30 pm.

Defendant Ryan D Jarosinski in court with attorney Mark Jay Gumz.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Court questions Atty Gumz regarding the criminal complaint.  Atty Gumz states that he is not sure if the defendant received it or not but the defendant would be prepared to proceed.
Atty Hendee requests a $250 cash bond with conditions due to the defendant was out on bond already.
Atty Gumz responds and requests a signature bond with the Absolute Sobriety condition.

BY THE COURT:  Court sets a $250 cash bond with conditions:
*Absolute Sobriety; zero tolerance  Initial appearance scheduled for September 14, 2015 at 01:00 pm.
